  "prompt": "What is the function of right dorsolateral prefrontal cortex?",
  "response": "The right dorsolateral prefrontal cortex (DLPFC) plays several important cognitive and executive functions:\n\n1. Cognitive Functions:\n- Working memory\n- Executive control\n- Attention regulation\n- Decision-making\n- Cognitive flexibility\n- Problem-solving\n\n2. Emotional Regulation:\n- Emotional processing\n- Emotion regulation\n- Inhibiting inappropriate emotional responses\n- Modulating emotional experiences\n\n3. Neurological Processes:\n- Spatial working memory\n- Spatial attention\n- Spatial reasoning\n- Spatial planning\n\n4. Specific Roles:\n- Goal-directed behavior\n- Planning complex cognitive tasks\n- Organizing and sequencing actions\n- Monitoring task performance\n\n5. Psychiatric and Neurological Implications:\n- Disruptions associated with conditions like:\n  - Depression\n  - Schizophrenia\n  - Attention deficit disorders\n  - Traumatic brain injuries\n\n6. Neuroplasticity:\n- Involved in learning and adaptation\n- Contributes to cognitive skill development\n- Supports neural network reorganization\n\nThe right DLPFC is particularly important for integrating cognitive and emotional processes, helping individuals manage complex mental tasks and regulate emotional responses.",
